Drew Carey said he decided to forgive the guy who’s been charged with the alleged murder of his ex-fiancee, Dr. Amie Harwick.
“After Amie’s [Harwick’s] murder, I took a week off,” the 61-year-old host of the “Price Is Right” shared during a pre-recorded interview for “The Talk.” The clip was noted by Page Six in a piece published Friday.
(RELATED: Wendy Williams Faces Backlash After Appearing To Mock Death Of Drew Carey’s Ex-Fiancé Dr. Amie Harwick)Why Drew Carey forgave ex-fiancée Amie Harwick’s alleged murderer https://t.co/lnhSRJN01Z pic.twitter.com/ecmOcGSYRr — Page Six (@PageSix) April 17, 2020“Really, I couldn’t function,” he added, before explaining that when he finally got back to the show it was “Kids Week” and he took the opportunity to speak with high school kids about forgiving Harwick’s alleged murderer, Gareth Pursehouse.
(RELATED: Drew Carey To Host Fundraiser For Gary Johnson)“I talked to them about how I forgave the guy who murdered Amie,” Carey shared.
“It would be so easy to carry around … every day think about revenge, which is not coming,” Drew said.